Feature: Integral Collective Five-Subsystem Operations

  As an Integral Collective node
  I want all five subsystems operating in coordinated sequence
  So that governance, strategy, innovation, and resource allocation work as one coherent system

  Background:
    Given OAD: Open Architecture Design (strategy layer)
    And ITC: Integral TRIZ Constructor (innovation layer)
    And CDS: Collective Decision System (governance layer)
    And COS: Commons Operating System (resource layer)
    And FRS: Federation Rules System (protocol layer)

  Scenario: OAD drives ITC to identify innovation opportunity
    Given OAD identifies a regeneration gap in water management
    When OAD sends strategic assessment to ITC
    Then ITC applies TRIZ contradiction analysis
    And identifies novel solutions using 40 inventive principles
    And returns solution candidates to OAD

  Scenario: ITC triggers CDS for governance decision
    Given ITC proposes a novel water management approach
    When ITC sends solution proposal to CDS
    Then CDS runs consensus-building across participants
    And evaluates evidence-based performance criteria
    And returns governance approval or refinement requests

  Scenario: CDS assigns to COS for resource operation
    Given CDS approves the water management approach
    When CDS assigns the task to COS
    Then COS tracks resource allocation for the task
    And COS monitors resource usage against plan
    And COS reports resource metrics to CDS

  Scenario: COS realizes through FRS protocol compliance
    Given COS allocates resources for the water project
    When the protocol runs through FRS
    Then FRS validates compliance with federation rules
    And FRS checks Ostrom principle alignment
    And FRS reports compliance status to COS

  Scenario: FRS influences OAD for next cycle
    Given FRS completes compliance validation
    When FRS sends feedback to OAD
    Then OAD incorporates outcomes into next strategy cycle
    And the five-subsystem loop continues
    And the system evolves through evidence-based feedback

  Scenario: Egregore competition within Integral Collective
    Given multiple Egregores proposing different approaches
    When each Egregore's approach is measured on outcomes
    Then influence flows to what's working
    And losing approaches fade and stop replicating
    And successful approaches gain influence and spread
    And no single Egregore can dominate

  Scenario: Post-monetary exchange within COS
    Given community members contribute to commons
    When the contribution is verified by CDS evidence
    Then COS records the contribution as value
    And value flows back as resource access rights
    And no traditional currency is required for exchange
